\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid5470496 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Bernera, Westbury Road, Great Holland, Near Frinton-on-Sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And you are married. The year of your marriage, please.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 1931.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 1905.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And your birth place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Graham Road, Hackney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 How many years did you live in that house where you were born, in Graham Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 This is something I'm not sure about. I should imagine that we had quite a number of addresses round about that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What influenced your moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The fact that my father lost his job when I was quite a small baby, 
and this necessitated smaller premises for economic conditions and from a flat it became rooms and things went, really, from bad to worse, for quite a number of years. What happened then was ... I just can faintly remember - although as I said earlier thi
s
 has probably been conditioned by what I've been told subsequently - that things got so bad that there was a time when I really was crying because I was hungry and there was no food and stuff in the house. And it was through the good offices of a friend o
f the church that my father really got put on his feet again and introduced to an employer, Badger }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2184773 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
 Co., the confectioners, where he obtained another situation. At the time we were living in Richmond Road, Dalston and we lived there a great number of years
, in point of fact until the First World War started. I'm sorry, I must correct that; until about 2 years before the Great World War started. We then moved at that time to South Chingford and we lived at the foot of Chingford Mount.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And was that until after the end of the War that you lived there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
No, during the War we came back again and, strangely enough, came back to the same rooms or flat that we had ... that we'd moved from previously in Richmond Road, Dalston.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I see, so you went from Richmond Road to Chingford and then back to the same place in Richmond Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 How old were you when your father got that situation with the confectioners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I'll guess. Say, seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And so really that first 7 years, roughly speaking, of your life was tough? That was the tough time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That's right, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And you would say that you moved several times then, but you're not sure how often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would it have been all round ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 All round the same area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You had, you said a sister, which you lost when you were about 3, or she was about 3?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When I was about 3.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 How old would she have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 She died between 9 and 12 months with Meningitis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And then another brother was born, in about what year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 1915. '14 -'15.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
My father was 2 years younger than my mother and at the time that I was born he was 19, I should say. It was a runaway marriage. Both my parents ran away 
from home because of conditions there and ... Well, they were very much in love and they set up home together on just what very little they could scrape together. That's why, when the shock came of losing a job there was nothing behind them at all to supp
ort them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And you say your mother was 19?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Your father was 19?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, Mother would have been 21.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Where did your father come from, was he a Londoner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, his home was at Finsbury Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And his occupation? Now, you said in 1911 he was a clerk. What was the job he got with the confectioners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Same sort of thing, clerk-typist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And the job that he lost, was that also a clerk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, it would be the same all the way through. Only, of course, he'd be more junior.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you know if he ever had a job, say, manual work or that type of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you know if he ever had any casual jobs or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Those years when he was out of work did he not do anything like that then, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think it was very, very difficult to get anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Now it say, 'do you ever remember your father being out of work'; do you have conscious memories of that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Could you tell me anything more about it? Do you remember your parents discussing it, the hardness of the times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
No, because parents in those days, particularly parents of the type that I had, very little was said in front of the children. There was the family sort of adage right the way down from g
randparents onwards 'little pigs have big ears' and all sorts of things were kept from them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And yet you were aware of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I was aware that there was shortage, and that one couldn't have the halfpenny or penny when one wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was your father at home a lot? Did he spend those unemployed days ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You see, up 'til 1911 I was only 6.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So you wouldn't remember very much about that. Now your mother, you said, was actually born in Yorkshire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. I couldn't tell you where.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did she meet your father in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Had she any jobs before she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Mother spent most of her teenage life in service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And after she was married did she ever have paid employment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What period are we talking about, up to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Up to 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Only ... up to that point it would be casual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What sort of work, cleaning? That type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Domestic work, yes, cooking. Cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But daily? She didn't ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And then after 1918, did she do any work after that period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Oh, yes, because you see, in 1923 my father's accident occurred and we tried all sorts of things, then. She had a boarding establishment; prior to that she set up a dressmaking business because she was quite a good dres
smaker, and that failed. That was a complete failure. But the boarding establishment went on for quite a long while. It was work like that, she had, mostly.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That sort of thing to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Can you remember her going out to work when you were quite a young child, so that you had to be looked after by somebody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. My recollections are more of her going out to work during the First World War, and I had to look after her!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, she was at work 
all day and I had to keep house. My father was in the Army and there were just the two of us, and we were back in Richmond Road, and I had to kind of do the chores, and that sort of thing. I had to go and queue up for the bread and the meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 As well as going to school you had to ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 As well as going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But your little brother, your much younger brother, would have been born by then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, by then he was born and my grandmother, who lived in Walthamstow, looked after him for qui
te a lot of the time. We used to go over at weekends. But during the week either my grandmother or one of my aunties - it was a large family - looked after him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 In their own home, he sort of stayed there, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 In their own home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And did your mother work full time, then, during the War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes. She was a shop assistant then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And your father was he away right through the War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, he was away through most of the War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Perhaps you could describe to me what type o
f accommodation it was in both of the places. I mean by that, what rooms there were, and where the family slept and that type of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The houses in Richmond Road were very large houses. They had at one time been gentry houses, occupied by gentry. T
here was a semi-basement with area steps leading down to a bottom door, very wide stone steps with stone pillars holding up the porch leading to the main hall. Very large rooms, as I remember them in the front of the house, and quite reasonable sized room
s
 as the bedrooms at the back. Starting with the semi-basement floor, counting that as semi-basement, then came the first floor, second floor ... Yes, there were 3 floors. And to start with when we first lived ... when I was very small when we first lived 
in Richmond Road, we had the top floor, which consisted of one large room - which was our }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
 - one large bedroom, and a reasonable sized room which we used as a kitchen. Also on this top floor there was a fairly large square landing. And that was o
ur home until we moved away just 2 years before the First World War, to Chingford. When we came back we had that same accommodation, but we also had an extra room on the floor below.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you have a bathroom at all in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. In the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was there one in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Not to my knowledge, no. What used to happen for both washing and bathing was an arrangement with the person living downstairs, the landlady, whereby she did her washing on the Monday morning and Mother did her wash
ing on the Tuesday morning, and any time that was wanted for bathing there was a very large galvanised bath which was brought in from outside in the garden into the scullery, as they called it, where the copper was and you just lit the copper and ... I th
ink it was Thursday night or Friday night ... Yes, our night was Friday night and they used to bath on Saturday nights. And that's how it was done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And that was in the landlady's quarters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That was in the landlady's quarters, this scullery that led off her kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was she quite an accommodating sort of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, she was a very nice sort of person, yes. We got on quite well with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That must have made quite a difference to your mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, although it's rather surprising
. It shows how accommodating she must have been because they were poles apart in their outlook upon life and in their ideas of ... shall we say moralities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. I mean, my mother, for instance, was very bigoted against drink but the p
eople downstairs, the Woods, they frequented the public houses and that was their main occupation on Saturdays and Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were they the worse for it, do you think, or did they just have ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I've never seen them what I might call reeling drunk
, although Mr. Woods was very uncertain-tempered when he had had quite a lot to drink. In those days quite a lot of working class people did odd work and two of their daughters used to work as barmaids in the hostelry that they favoured.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did your mother think that regrettable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was that a family tradition of your mother's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, no, her own parents and that were ... her father, particularly, was very much addicted to drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So it was a reaction, possibly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It was a reaction and a nonconformist conscience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was she, would you say, a strict person in other ways as well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Very. Very. Today one would say that she was prudish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you think in those times there were many like her that you'd sort of meet and ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 ... Get to know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 More than there are now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, I think so. Definitely. This was the strict Victorian outlook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did your father have the same sort of outlook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, but Father wasn't quite so forceful as my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 She was the stronger personality, was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 She was the dominating personality.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 In the house in Chingford, did you have any more space there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. This was different altogether. This was more of a country ... little 
country house. It was a terraced house, but we were the end and we had a side entrance and here we had the usual six rooms that you find in the normal modern house. We didn't occupy the whole of the house for quite a number of years, or for quite a time. 
W
e had an elderly lady living with us who had one back room. This was quite common in those days when there weren't very many old people's homes. They used to find a family that would be prepared to have them, and live for a few shillings in one of the bac
k rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did she do anything for you, or did you do anything for her, other than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 She was quite independent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, she was independent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What did she do about cooking and that type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They usually had an oil stove in their room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did she share any facilities like taps and toilets, and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, she would have to for toilets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But not washing facilities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And a bathroom. We had a bathroom in this Chingford house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And she used that, too, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So you would call her a lodger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 A lodger, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
That covers one of my questions which is whether, beside your own particular family, you had any relatives or lodgers living with you. Would you say that was the only one in those years up to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And the grannies and aunts were never actually part of the household?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Can you remember ... I'm not sure if you told me earlier why it was you moved to Chingford. Did you mention it or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
No, I didn't mention it. I think it was a desire on my parents part to get away from a locality that they had been so used to all their life, and to get out into the country a little more where housing was proportionately cheaper, and cost of
 living cheaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And then why did they move back, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When Father had to go into the Forces Mother went back to be nearer her relatives and friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did she send her washing out or was it done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did your mother or father make any clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 My mother used to do quite a lot. As I said earlier, she was quite a capable dressmaker, and so she would make for herself and, particularl
y, for me. Pairs of trousers and blouses, and things, you know, these sailor blouses that the boys used to wear so much in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did she ever make anything like a suit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Only when I was very small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were any clothes bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, yes, they would have to be, but where they came from, how frequently they were purchased I really don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You don't remember going to buy ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I can remember ... you know ... It was mostly a pair of breeches. When I was at school in Chingfor
d I seem to remember we wore those breeches that button just below the knee, and a jersey, something of that nature. And a coat over the top if it was very cold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And you think those clothes would have been bought by the time you went to school in Chingford?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about mending, did she do mending?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Yes, she was quite good at mending with the needle, and that, and she looked after both Father and myself and saw that our clothes were in good condition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did he do any sewing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Who? My father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. He was like me, I can't handle a needle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about repairing shoes, did he ever repair shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, I don't think he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Who did the repairs of shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, a snob, as they called them. The old cobbler, the village cobbler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You don't remember whether clothes were bought for particular occasions, particular seasons, that you don't recall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Money was very, very short even in those days and so long as you had, shall we say, a suit
 of clothes for the weekday and - here again, convention - a best set of clothes for Sunday, you were considered to be adequately dressed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you know if clothes would be bought at any particular seasons, like Easter or Whitsun?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. The only tim
e I can remember when one had a shopping expedition to buy clothes was when the relatives died and there was the customary black that we went out and bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember a particular relative dying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 My grandfather. On my mother's side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you wear that black for some time afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Any idea how long? Because mourning customs and the way they change are very interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Until the suit or whatever I had ... I think I had a coat. Well, it would be until that coat was worn out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And your mother had black, too, then, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Oh, yes, Mother ... The daughters usually had these small insurances for which they paid so much per week, the industrial insurance, and this was to provide them with their black at the time of a death in the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did she have sort of crepe, and that type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you go to that funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 As a matter of fact I did. It was my first funeral that I'd ever attended. Why I went I don't know,
 because I lived in mortal fear of this grandfather. At any rate, I went to this funeral and I can remember that everybody cried, so much so that I cried, myself. On the other hand it was a nice ride in the carriages behind the plumed horses (laughter).

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you have a sort of tea afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That would be at my grandmother's house, in Walthamstow, from where the funeral took place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was it just relatives, or was it friends as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Mostly relatives, 
but my grandfather had a lot of acquaintances. He was a very good cricketer and so some of his cricketing friends came to the funeral. Also, he was chairman of the local Conservative and Unionist Party and there again, that gave him quite a following. Alt
hough he'd taken no active part in either cricket or politics for some years, as he had cancer and had been very ill for many years, or several years, before he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember anything else about the funeral; whether there were other children there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, I think I was the only child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you find it a sort of awesome occasion at all, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, terribly solemn, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were there other funerals? You didn't presumably go to your sister's funeral, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, no. I can't remember that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs inside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Yes. He was ... I wouldn't say very domesticated, but I can remember that he was quite capable if Mother wasn't well of getting my breakfast and seeing 
me off to school. He'd help her with washing up and clearing up and, whilst we were poor, we were quite a happy little family. We used to go out quite a lot Saturday afternoons, and that, on picnics and that sort of thing, particularly when we lived at Ch
i
ngford. Because it was unspoiled in those days and there were lovely meadows and woods and places like that. And they were both good walkers and they taught me to enjoy walking. Incidentally, I met my wife, because she lived 3 doors away from me in the co
ttages at Chingford, at the bottom of ... and I used to take her to school in those days and bring her home again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So the move to Chingford was a good one for you! When you set out on an excursion from Chingford would it be on foot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 On foot the whole time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Unless you were coming into London direction, when there were some really old bumpy trams that stopped and had their terminus at Chingford Mount. And they went as far as the Baker's Arms, Leyton.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So if you were going into London you'd get a bus?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You'd get this tram up to Hoe Street Station and then you'd get the train to London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But otherwise, for your picnics and things it was all on foot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 On foot. There were no buses or anything going up Chingford Moun
t in those days, it was considered far too steep for a bus to get up the Mount. When we first lived there it was a narrow lane and there were great trees that used to arch it and meet in the middle. And whilst we were children there - I'm talking about my
 wife and myself - the whole of the hill was altered. They took the top off and filled in the bottom with the top, as it were, so as to alter the gradient of the hill and they widened it, took all the trees down and then they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 eventually}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  got buses running up
. So after about 1916, I suppose, they'd got buses running up the hill so you could start out and get a bus from Chingford, say, through to High Beech. I may be a little bit out with my dates, but roughly then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And when you were still in Richmond Road where would you go for an outing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Funnily enough, the favourite place for taking children for excursions or out for the Saturday would be Chingford or thereabouts. Hampstead was the other place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would you go for the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, you would go for the day, usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Take something with you to eat, would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What sort of thing would you take in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, sandwiches. Very much as we do today, ham sandwiches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And a flask of something, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Usually lemonade in a bottle, I think, for the children at any rate. We used to go off on our own, sometimes, as children. Our favourite was taking just cold water and sherbert powder or lemonade powder and making our own drink with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I don't know Hackney very well. Victoria Park is about the nearest park, was that the nearest sort of park to where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, really. There was Hackney Downs which you can see on the railway line, the Chingford line, if you're going up, and there was also 
another open space known as London Fields which is nearer to Bethnal Green.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you go to all those places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I have been, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 As a child you used to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So you would say you were out quite a lot at weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Reasonably
. Of course we had a garden and at the bottom of our garden it was hay fields then and meadows pretty well right the way across to Edmonton, then, and we weren't enclosed with houses at all. Nowadays it's all built, those fields have gone completely.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember your father ever doing any cooking? You said he'd get breakfast, do you ever remember him cooking dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, not in those early years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And after 1918 did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, when he had recovered somewhat from his accident and was n
ot quite so unpredictable, one of the occupations he liked and which made him feel a little more secure, that he was doing something for his living, was to help in the house and he used to do quite a lot then, to help my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And in the early years was he able to do things like decorating, or was that landlady's responsibility?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Usually the landlord or landlady's responsibility, and very little was done in those days in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not like it is today, changing all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Nowhere n
ear. I can remember when my grandmother in her house at Walthamstow, her daughters had been on at her how dirty the ceiling was in her kitchen and I can remember their attempt at doing it. They hadn't any tools, brushes, or anything to do it with, so they
 
made up some whitening and blued it with an ordinary blue bag, washing blue bag and then, having nothing better to do it with they got the ordinary sweeping broom, dipped that in the bowl of whitewash that they made and just striped it across the ceiling,
 backwards and forwards (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So you don't remember your father doing any decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about repairs, do-it-yourself improvements, anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I don't think any of this was done by the normal person until ... well,
 after about the Second World War. It's since so many people have got houses of their own that this has started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And shorter working hours, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And shorter working hours. Young people, as far as I remember them when I was a teenager, s
hall we say, and later ... well, they were content with rooms to start married life in. There was none of this wanting a house with all its fittings, and things, when you started marriage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember your father looking after you, personally, as a child? Putting you to bed, giving you a bath on Thursday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, I think he had done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about telling you stories or reading to you, did he do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, he was very good, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 He liked that sort of thing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 He liked that sort of thing, and he encouraged you to do things for yourself and he'd help you to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What kind of things, particularly, would he encourage you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I've always had a bit of an imagination, quite a vivid one from time to time and I used t
o fancy myself that I could write things and he would encourage me to do it. The consequence was that at school I was usually well up to the top of the class, if not the top, for essays and compositions and English generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 He'd actually encourage you to write things down, and would he read them himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What sort of subjects would that be when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 Far more simple than they would be today, I mean, it would be ... For instance, I visited exhibitions and at 
the end of the War I went to the People's Palace to see an aeronautical exhibition and there were quite a number of things there like Sopworth's planes and a German Torb, and things like that, and I won a prize for an essay on that exhibition, on the visi
t to that exhibition; and generally, the school subjects for essays were around that standard; essays on visits to places of interest, or how you spent your weekends, or imaginary conversations with a rubber ball, or something else.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 A day in the life of a pea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That's the thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not sort of fantastical or magical sort of subjects?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about actually reading stories to you, did he do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, not very much, I didn't require it. I was rather a prodigious reader, myself, and other things suffered because of my habit of reading.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were you quite an early reader?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What sort of age, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, as soon as I could form letters and pronounce words, then I liked reading and I would read anything and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you have books in the house or were they got from outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I had quite a number of books as presents and there were books in the house. But of course, the books in the house were very much edited by my mother. I was only allowed to read good books and I was only allowed to read religious books on Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When you say they were edited you mean there were books which she wouldn't let you read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, of course, she herself was a very great reader and she would read books that she wouldn't consider suitable for me to read.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember any one in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I can't think of titles of books, exactly, but if a book was ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Any authors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, I mean, I used to read R.M. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 Ballantyne}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  and Henty and all the boys' writers, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you read ones like Talbot Baines Read and those sort of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That's right, yes. Yes. And 'Coral Island', you see, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 Ballantyne}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 Fennimore}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  Cooper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Robert Louis Stevenson?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Robert Louis Stevenson. Th
ey were quite all right, and I used to take the Scout and Boys' Own Paper, that was the one I was trying to think of. I used to have that occasionally. And, of course, I used to have 'Chatterbox Annual'. Those were the standard sort of books and I used to
 
read as much as I liked of that, or I could read history books. Libraries were mostly, I think, in those days kind of Sunday school libraries and the like. The public library, as far as I can remember, wasn't used very much by my parents or myself. It was
n't until I was much older that I realized the value of a good public library.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was your father a reader too, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Your mother was the reader?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Mother was the reader and I followed in her footsteps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember any authors that she particularly enjoyed? Did she read people like Marie }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 Corelli}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  and Mrs. Humphrey Ward.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes. Mrs. Henry Wood, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, Mrs. Henry Wood. What about the great classics of the 19th century, do you think she read those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Dickens, she would read. Dickens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were you allowed to read Dickens, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I had a book of Dickens', but it was mostly an edited children's edition. It took ... like, Little Nell, the crossing sweeper, out and put it as the thing on its own; and as far as Nicholas Nickleby was concerned you get ... }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3103133\charrsid7630904 D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 otheboys' }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3103133\charrsid7630904 H}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
all episode, but it was an isolated story. This is up to 1918 we're talking about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you know if your mother read George Eliot and Charlotte Bronte and those sort of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. George Eliot was 'The Mill on The Floss'?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, I can remember seeing that, that book and, of course, the Brontes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So she had very wide tastes, both the classics and the more popular ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about poetry, at all? Was poetry read in the family, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Just for the sake of the recording they were presented in 1912, each with a book of poetry. Your mother was the Longfellow, was it, and your father the Tennyson?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The other way round. Father was Longfellow and Mother the Tennyson. And this is for the work that they used to do amongst cripples in the }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 Haggerston}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  slums under the auspices of the Shaftesbury Society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Had they been doing that for some years or was it quite ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Yes. They were always interested in mission work and being interested they really did social service as we call it today. They were visitors to these crippled children in these slum homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 In their own family home, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 In their famil
y home, yes, they would visit them and they worked with the Shaftesbury Society, who used to be able to give financial help and holidays and things like that to these crippled children in their families if it was required.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was that the sort of thing that took up quite a lot of their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I think Mother ... Yes, Mother spent quite a lot of time, and my father also just prior to his accident, was very much engaged in it for two or 3 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were there any other mission work or social work things that they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Well, this seemed to be their main ... hobby, their main activity. They were interested in this mission work and ... Mother was interested in Guides.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was she a Guider?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, she was a Guider.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 She had a troop, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 A company. A company.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were you a Scout, or a Cub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
A Cub, a Scout, and a Lone Rover. There was no Rover troop and yet I was a Rover Scout in the district and so I acted as kind of an assistant to the Scout master.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was that in Chingford?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, that was in Hackney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Before you went ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, after. After. When we came back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I was asking you about reading. Do you remember them actually reading those books? Those books were read, the Tennyson and the Longfellow?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Your mother was particularly fond of poetry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When your brother was born did you have any jobs or duties to look after him in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 As well as the aunts and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 granny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  you also had to look after him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Yes. When we moved back ... Well, after he was born. There, from that stage onwards there were certain things that fell to my lot always to do. With this mission work, and that, that my parents were interested in they were frequently o
ut at evenings and I was the official baby-sitter, and I had to look after him. It's true that whilst the War was on and he was quite a young baby he was with my grandparents, but soon as the War was finished we still continued to live in this Richmond Ro
a
d house for quite ... several years, and Mother and Father went out to their mission interests and I had to stay home of an evening and look after him which entailed kind of putting him to bed and ... If there was any trouble I could always go downstairs 
to the landlady and Mother knew that, that we were both safe enough in the house. But, yes, I had to do quite a lot for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Quite a lot of responsibility?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Quite a lot of responsibility. And this went on from that stage onwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Up until he was quite big, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember what you felt about it at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Just accepted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you find it irksome?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I don't think so, it was someone to play with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You liked him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I liked him, yes. Oh, yes. We
 were very adventuresome because I can remember at quite an early age I had a bicycle, I used to sit him on the carrier at the back and come over as far as Connaught Waters and have a boat out and go ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Take him out in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Take him out. Consider myself quite the big brother, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So you quite enjoyed, you say, looking after him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes. I expect there were times when I felt like murdering him (laughter) but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember actually taking him out for an airing in the pram, or anything like that? When he was a baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Oh, yes, I pushed him about. In fact, I shot him out of his pram, once, I remember that, somehow got the angle of the pram wrong as I was walking along the pavement, I suppose a couple of the wheels went over the curb and over he went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about your father, did he also take him out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes. Yes. It was unusual, perhaps, in those days. Men didn't do it so much as they do today, but Dad did take him out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember when he was 4 or 
5 did your brother do things for you, did he help you with anything, deliver messages for you? Or was it all more on your side, for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, I suppose if he was asked to do anything he would try to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 There was that sort of easy relationship between the two of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Now, as a child, thinking back as far as you can remember, were you actually put to bed or did you take yourself off to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, of course, at a very early age I was put to bed, but I was taught, al
ways, to be self-reliant, which meant as soon as I was able to do things for myself I was expected to do them. And, to go on from there, not only to do things for myself but to do things for other people, as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So you put yourself to bed at quite an early age, you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would your mother then come in and see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, come and say good-night, and see that I had put my clothes up tidily and washed my face and my hands, not gone to bed dirty.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 In the house in Richmond Road there was the one bedroom. Did you all sleep in the one room? I think you said there was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 , a bedroom and a kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, I did, didn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Because you said when you came back you had another room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When we came back we had another room, which meant that I had the little room upstairs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 All to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, and we'd come down ... I think we had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 dining room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  downstairs. That's right, a room that we had as a general }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
. Yes, we must have done because at that time Mother bought a piano and I remember that went up into the very top of the house, into what had been our }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 , that now became our - as we would call it today - our lounge, our parlour. And when I got a little older, you see, of course then I 
had this ... I slept out of my parents' room. But as a very small child I must have slept in my parents' room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And in Chingford, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I had my own room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When your brother was born did you share with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The same bed, or just the same room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Same bed, most of the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Now, we talked about the arrangements for bathing in those days. How often did you have a clean set of clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Thinking about the house in Richmond Road, did you eat in the kitchen where the gas cooking was done? You mentioned a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 dining room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  but I think you said that was when you got back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 In Richmond Road, if I remember rightly ... Yes, it was right. The cooker, the gas cooker was on 
this big landing that I told you about, so the kitchen was definitely a kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, if I had a party, or at Christmas time when the table was laid up for a festive occasion it was done in the best room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you call it the best room, or what was the name given to it in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
If you had a house then usually the best room was called either 'the front room' or 'the parlour'. If you lived in rooms, as we did, well you called it 'the best room'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You had a gas cooker, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Gas cooker, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And thinking, now, about Richmond Road, you'd have your meals in the kitchen. Did you have breakfast? I mean a sort of sit-down breakfast?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And what sort of things did you have to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 For breakfast, porridge which was made from coarse oatmeal, not Quaker Oats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So it was prepared overnight, was it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It was prepared overnight. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 Or semolina. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Weekends you might have a sausage. It was bread and
 dripping; bread and marmalade. Weekends, an egg, sausage, sometimes a bit of bacon. Fried bread was always a great favourite, and toast. Toast, of course, was made from an ordinary open fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 On a fork, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 On a fork, and it was
 usually my job to do the toast. I was going to say that if one had bread and marmalade or bread and jam at tea, it really was bread and jam. The butter was omitted. You could have either bread and butter or bread and jam, you didn't have both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You did have butter, did you, even at the hardest times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. One talks of butter, but invariably it was margarine. I think I can even remember the brand, it was Kilos, and it came from the Home }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2184773 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  Colonial. That's my commercial (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When you say it was weekends, different breakfasts, would you include Saturday, as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, only Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Because, presumably when your father got a job again he went to work on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Can you remember whether you had tea or coffee to drink at Breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It would be tea, or else milk. Coffee was a rarity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And you did have drinks of milk, did you? Glasses or cups of milk as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I suppose I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You don't actually recollect it, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. In the Chingfo
rd days I can remember that milk was probably a little bit more obtainable then because we used to be a few doors away from a farm and we used to go up to the farm with our great big cans and get our milk. Whether it was cheaper getting it from the farm r
ather than in the town from the milkman ... I seem to think we had more milk in those days than we did when ... in the early days at Richmond Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about a midday meal, did you have a cooked meal at midday, or not? When you were in Richmond Road, and Chingford, too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Yes, as far as possible Mother tried to give a hot meal. And of course, as far as Father was concerned, usually Father's meal was kept and hotted up again for him at night. But the meals were rather sparse, 2 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 penn'orth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  of bones st
ewed down into broth with peas and lentils, and that, made a real good soup. Stews and soups and occasional meat puddings were the things most frequently on the menu. Even weekends it was often a steak pie, we didn't seem to run to joints, and that, a lot
. Certain offal like pigs' fry and liver and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But soup would sometimes be the main meal, would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The main meal, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would you have ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Boiled mutton was a favourite. I can remember this, boiled mutton and pearl barley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 As a soup, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, as a soup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And if you had that would you have any other vegetables as well, or would that be the dish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, it would be pot herbs; carrots, onions, turnip ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 In this dish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 In with the soup, and potato.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you have a pudding, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Yes, we did have puddings quite frequently and I've always loved puddings ever since, you know golden pudding and a plum pudding and so on. At Chingford, you see, we had this garden and we used to gro
w quite a bit in the way of cabbages and carrots and the like, and beans, which supplemented the family income and gave us vegetables that we might not have had if we'd still lived in town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But in town you did have vegetables sometimes, as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Though no place to grow anything, I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. There was a garden but it was beyond cultivation, worn out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Your father never came home at midday, I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And his meal would be saved for him in the evening; and then would he eat that meal with the rest of you, or would be have it on his own?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Depends what time he was home, you see, if he was working late, a bit of overtime or something like that, then that would colour it. But quite frequently ... Well, I th
ink I had my tea first, when I came in from school and perhaps I would have my last little supper drink with my father as he had his meal. I think that's more likely what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What time would he usually get in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Seven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You say on Sundays you didn't have a joint very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not very often, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would you say you had one occasionally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Occasionally, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you have anything different at all on a Sunday? If you didn't have a joint would there be anything differ
ent at dinner or tea to make it a bit different?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, I think occasionally, a kipper, perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Your mother did cook on a Sunday, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I just wondered if she believed it wrong to work at all on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, I think we'
d put the dinner in the oven, and that sort of thing. Of course, in those days it was kitchen ranges and you would leave the fire and stuff in and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember if she did anything like baking bread or making jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Make jam, definitely. We used to go blackberrying and all that sort of thing. She would make jams and preserves ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Even when you were still in Hackney?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, we'd go out for the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And what about baking, do you ever remember her baking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. Mother was quite a good cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 She's tried bread, I wouldn't say she was successful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And making pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, do preserves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 She did do that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about making wine or beer? She wouldn't have done that, presumably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They have made homemade wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I can always remember them thinking they'd got burglars in the house one night when the yeast worked and blew the corks out of the bottles and made a terrific clatter downstairs. (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Now, that seems a little strange. How do you account for her making the wine when she was such a very anti-drink person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 This is one of those inconsistencies of all people who say they're teetotalers My mother at Christmas time or on a wedding 
occasion or something like that would concede to drinking a small glass of port, and yet she's a ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And you think that making the wine was just a little ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I don't think they really knew that yeast fermented to the extent that it did and that it could produce an alcoholic condition.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you know if theirs was quite a strong sort of wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I don't think they tried it after this. This was the one experiment that didn't really come off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about any beer, did she ever try beer at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And making any medicines, did she make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Cough mixtures and an indigestion mixture would be about the full extent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Now, in Hackney they didn't grow anything, but they did in Chingford? You said vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about fruit trees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No fruit trees; there may have been some raspberry canes, that would be about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did they keep any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not even in Chingford?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember if they ever got any extra meat, such as rabbit, from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Never!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 How many times a week would you say they ate meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Are you counting stews as meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I'm counting any meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, if there was a joint on Sunday you would have it on Sunday; had it cold on 
Monday; probably was in the form of a Shepherd's Pie, or something by Tuesday. Then Wednesday you'd probably have your bone soup, which would do Wednesday and Thursday, and probably Friday there would be cheese. Saturday dinner was always a makeshift dinn
er.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I wanted to ask you if you remember eating tinned meat at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Yes. Not that we would buy a tin of meat, one would go to the grocer and buy a quarter of corned beef which was tinned corned beef, and that's about all I can remember, in the way of tinned meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember actually realizing that your mother was ever having less food so that the others could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 We were rather a peculiar family in this respect, I suppose I got the best of most things. My mother and father sh
ared equally. My father was a very obstinate man and if he thought that my mother hadn't got her share he would make sure that they got more or less equal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I see. He wasn't the sort of man who wanted a bigger helping. Now I'd like to ask you somethin
g about behaviour at table: were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, unless we had company. Then I was expected to speak when I was spoken to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
If a thing was on the table it was there to be eaten and ... For instance, if at teatime I wanted jam and there was no jam on the table, or something else to go on the bread, fishpaste, or something, I had to eat what was there. I wasn't given 
in to because I fancied something else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And if there was some food actually left what would their attitude be? If you left food on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You mean my food on my plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, if it was a question just of sulks on my part beca
use I didn't particularly like it they used to try and say, 'well, it'll be served up for your breakfast', or the next meal, and sometimes it was, but it was never really enforced.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You don't remember an occasion of it coming back for more than one meal? I mean coming back through the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 If there was something on the table that you wanted which was out of reach could you ask for it to be passed to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes. If I ... it was considered I'd had enough, then I was told so and that was the end of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But you could ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
And what about things like the way you sat at table, the way you held your knife and fork, do you remember any of that training if you had training in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Told
 to sit up straight in the chair, not to fidget, always use your knife in the right hand and so on. Just general table manners and I suppose they were, yes, rigidly enforced.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Could you ever bring a toy or a book to the table during mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 After I'd asked permission to leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would that be before your parents had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Could be. Could be.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You had to ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you all have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Usual sitting place, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Can you tell me how the meal was actually served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
It was dished up in the kitchen, normally, and brought in ready served on the plates. On special occasions vegetables might be put into a dish, but the meat was usually carved away from table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Can you remember when your little brother was very small how he managed for meals and how was he fed? When he was, say a year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 High chair at the side of the table next to Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 He had a high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Can you remember, if you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Corporal punishment, usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 From Mother and from Father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Mostly from Mother. She was a tartar (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would you say you were frequently punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Constantly checked. Mother had a very quick temper and she would often hit out before she thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember how you felt about that, if you had any sort of feeling about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Sometimes very wild 
about it, I felt it was unjust. And as I got a little older and could really think for myself the sense of injustice became even worse so that it led me to do silly things, 'cos I'm also quick-tempered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 By 'silly things' could you explain what you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Well, I walked out of the house one day and said 'if that's the way you're going to treat me I'm not stopping here' and out I went. Only to have Father come chasing after me and go back to even more of an uproar than before, but still (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were you made to apologise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Oh, yes, after Mother cooled down we kind of ... general sort of apologies all round. Yes, yes. There was never ... Don't misunderstand me, there was never any really rancour or bad feeling. Neither of us ... my fathe
r a little bit, but Mother no and me no, no sulky temper. It was over in a flash.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about any other type of punishment? Have you ever been deprived of things, that type of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, I never had very much in the way of pocket money or
 Saturday sweets, but I suppose occasionally that was stopped. I think Mother's attitude was more 'oh, well, wallop him and that's the end of it'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not being sent to bed without food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, being sent to bed, yes. Oh, yes, sent to bed early, usuall
y told it was going to be without supper but, you see, by the time she came up to bed or something she'd relented and if I was still awake then there'd perhaps be a drop of milk or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When she and your father were talking were you allowed to join in? When they were talking to friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
No. No, as I said I was expected to ... particularly with company. And if I interrupted when they were having a private conversation I'd be told. And of course, the thing that was said so often the
n when children were present when adults were speaking was 'little pigs with big ears'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You remember people actually saying that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Can you remember what they thought about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Horrified.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Really very strong feelings about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you ever remember picking up words in the neighbourhood and coming home with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I must have done. I think I must have done and ... I think I have got hazy recollections of coming out with improper things at times and being very severely choked off for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be, you and your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think they always cherished an ambition that a social class that I would eventually finish up in would be at least
 above the one that they started from, and to that end I think they did their best to do this. I've already said that there was a certain enforcement of discipline and general manners which was something perhaps she ... my mother had never been taught, he
rself. She'd picked it up from being in service and what was done in nice households and she tried to introduce it into her own and all the time she was looking for me to kind of improve my mind. She did her best as far as education was concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 By encouraging you at school, was that it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 As far as values in behaviour in a much wider sense was concerned, do you remember being aware of sort of values as a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, as I've said, it was a Christian home and basically there was a
 very strong moral atmosphere and it was these kind of Christian virtues that were always kind of put in front of you and, therefore, it took a very wide moral kind of outlook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would you say, thinking back to your childhood, that your mother was an easy person to get along with and talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
She's very easy in a general sense. Yes, most people got on very well with her and she was reckoned to be a good mixer and an extremely good visitor. But as I say, she had her temper and she was easily put out if somebody did say the wrong thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, very demonstrative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember having worries that you shared with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, we did, because my father had a nervous breakdown ... I'm trying to think how old
 I might have been, probably round about the 12 to 14 years of age, and we did share confidences a lot in that time because it was a very, very worrying period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was he off work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, he came off work through the illness and at one time he wandered off and was missing for 2 or 3 days because of loss of memory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did he actually have to leave home to go into a hospital?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. No. He recovered after a time and went back to his business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 How would you say that your parents expected y
ou to behave towards them? You've answered a lot of this already by implication, but do you remember anything in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, they expected obedience. That was the basic thing. And they expected me to respond to their plans for me and also to re
turn any affection that was shown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
When you say they expected you to return any affection you mean that they liked to feel that you felt close to them, they liked to be aware of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would you say that your father was the same as your mother in that way, demonstrative, affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, yes, he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember talking to him about problems you had or things you were worried or concerned about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I suppose I must have done. He used to play with me 
quite a lot as I grew up, and shared quite a lot of my interests. We were both slightly musical and that was a common interest. So I suppose I must have talked to him about most things. I don't think that it was in a very adult sort of way, I'm talking ab
out childhood.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But he was an approachable father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 These musical interests that you shared, what sort was that? Was that the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Violin. We both played violin at that time and then later ... it was not until later years that I learnt the piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Your mother had a piano when you moved back to Richmond Road, didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. No. Ah, yes, that was ... Now wait a minute, we're getting the periods confused. That was well after the Second World War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, it was some time after you ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 After the First World War, when we first came back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So that was when you moved back to Richmond Road, just for the records, about the second year of the War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Your father played games with you: was that indoor games and outdoor games? Can you tell me any of them that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, I mean, indoors .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3103133\charrsid7630904 .. he was a bit of a Draughts f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 iend, and we'd play all the usual table games like Snakes }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2184773 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
 Ladders, and Ludo and Halma and Draughts, Darts, anything like that. And outdoor games we would share with ball games, and flying a kite, anything of that nature which we used to do in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So he was quite a companion to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about your mother, did she play any games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, she'd join in, you know, if we were with a little party, gone out for a little picnic or anything, play }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 rounders}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 We talked quite a bit about books and reading but I didn't ask you whether you had a newspaper regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Could you tell me what it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The News Chronicle. It was The Daily News And Leader, in those days, before it amalgamated with The Chronicle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And any magazines that they subscribed to or got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I don't think they took a regular magazine although I believe Mother occasionally had ... Home Notes, I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about any Church magazines or parish ...?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, they didn't used to ... I know there's a parish magazine, a church magazine. If she had anything at all from the church, and it was
 a nonconformist church which wouldn't have a parish magazine it would be, say a missionary magazine, or something of that nature. It was called The Foreign Field, I think, the missionary magazine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And that did sometimes come, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You mentioned that sometimes, if you had a birthday you would eat in the best room, I think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Can you remember anything about birthdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Usually for birthdays Mother tried to extend herself a little bit and there was usually a li
ttle party of my friends and relatives, and usually a special tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Any present-giving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Yes, if ... usually, but of course, presents in those days often took the form of clothing and not so many of the fancy toys and things that you have today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave equally from both parents or would you say that one transmitted the values and attitudes more than the other, as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I should say equally, although home management, as a rule, was in the hands of my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember going out alone with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, frequently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 He would take you out would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Walks, and going various places and particularly if we arranged to go out, say, to a concert or some
thing and Mother wasn't well, the 2 of us would go alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 He took you to concerts, did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Occasionally because, you see ... There again, churches and that were constantly having social functions that were open to both children and adults.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
And going out visiting the relatives in Walthamstow, were they actually sort of paid visits as a regular thing, or wasn't it that kind of relationship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, they were regular visits. My mother was one of a fairly large family and it was quite the
 done thing, they all met together once a week, or so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And did they take you with them when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Most times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not until 1915 or '16. I can't be really sure of the date. When I saw the 
... my first visit to the seaside. I went to Southend and that was my first ... I may have been there before on a day trip as a Sunday School outing, but it was the first time we ever stayed away, at the seaside. And I know it was during the first part of
 the War because whilst we were there we were subjected to a daylight raid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I remember it very vividly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were you frightened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I must have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It must have been awful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. The 'planes came down, they drop
ped bombs in the daylight; they machine-gunned people on the beach and we were on the beach at the time, so there was a complete stampede from the beach. And there was a bomb dropped outside the house where we were staying. I believe it was in Victoria Ro
ad, Southend. And I know they burst the gas main and we ... I can still remember vividly that we were breathing gas all night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember anybody actually being injured?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I heard people were injured but I didn't actually see it, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You rushed back to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was it a boarding house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Only a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was that with just your mother or did your father ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Just Mother and myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was that before your younger brother was born? He was born round about then, wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It must have been before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember what you did, what the seaside activities were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Usual things; play with a bucket and spade. And we did go in to the Kursaal. Just the usual activities of a seaside ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did they have all the pier things then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They had the pier. We went on the pier, yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did that become a regular thing? Going away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not necessarily for the family. But after that occasion I usually went away quite frequently with a boy friend of mine.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 We stayed quite a number of times at Hemel Hempstead, that's near to Boxmore in Hertfordshire. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think that's mostly where we went, Hemel Hempstead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was that a boarding house, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
No, that was an old lady had a cottage down there, her and her aged husband and we used to go down .... I don't know where we got the address from or how we came to know them, but we went there year after year for several years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Again, for about a week, would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, we stayed longer. I should say a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That was in your school holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 School holiday periods, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was that a specially close friend of yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, I suppose he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 How did you spend Saturdays in those days? Do you remember how Saturdays went? Did you have a part time job at all, a Saturday job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. As a young boy I had certain errands to do on Saturday mornings. There were certain heavy things, art
icles of shopping like potatoes and things like that to be got from the shop. It was also my job to see that there was wood chopped, ready for the days of the week, kindling for the fire, and so on, and also I was supposed to clean the knives and silver, 
a job that I detested. I often got into trouble because I didn't do them properly. We had a knife board on which you shook the emery powder and then rubbed these steel knives up and down until you got them clean and shiny and sharp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was that quite a tedious job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
It was a very tedious job and a very hard job, particularly if the knives were badly stained. And then, of course, all silver ... all cutlery had to be cleaned, there was none of this stainless stuff that we have today, and you did it with
 plate powders and things like that and the thing was to get all th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3103133\charrsid7630904 at muck}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
 out between the prongs of the forks after you'd cleaned them. I wasn't very good at it and I think eventually, Mother used to get a bit tired of the time I took doing it and ... So,
 Saturday morning usually was full of little errands and chores and things like that to be done. Saturday afternoon according to the weather sometimes we would go out. Sometimes I just played with my friends on the road in the field, when we were at Ching
f
ord, particularly. Sometimes there were organised things that you could go to. Saturday evenings, if there was any recreation or a social or a concert or anything like that that had been arranged, you had to get certain other things ready for Sunday befor
e you went out to them. But otherwise, Saturday evenings were spent reading or playing or doing something or the other, but you were expected to have your shoes already cleaned for Sunday, and the bulk of the work was done on Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And then on the Sunday, can you describe to be the activities of a typical Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Well, we used to indulge a little bit Sunday mornings, you didn't have to get up quite so early. And then it was a case of getting breakfast over and getting ready and going off to mo
rning Service, coming back for lunch - or dinner, as it was. - After the midday meal, then off to Sunday School in the afternoon and usually, although not always, back to evening Service in the evening. Probably your other questions cover this, but there 
were restrictions on Sunday activities.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, I was coming to that. The question is did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Games had to be quiet games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Draughts and things were allowed, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What do you mean by quiet games, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I don't know as I really played much in the way of games. You see, your time was fairly full up. If there was time on a summer's evening, perhaps, after coming out of Sunday School we might go for walks, something of that n
ature. Quite frequently in nice weather we could go ... go out to tea to a relative's or to a friend's and that, again, took the time up. They were usually people who frequented church on an evening and so we all went together in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You'd go and have tea with Church friends, friends that you'd made through the Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, and then we'd got a common interest in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And only religious books, you mentioned last time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember any particular ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Oh, Bible stories, story of Joseph and books of that particular nature. I suppose I may have been a bit sweeping in saying only religious books: books that had quite a, shall we say a high tone to them were allowed, also.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You said that your parents were non-conformists, or you said that your mother was but I didn't ask you the denomination.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And your father, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were they regular attenders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Can you remember, was it from quite an early age that you went both to the services and the Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was that the usual thing at your particular chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It was the usual thing with all chapel-going people in those days, I think. To take the children. If the children were 
a bit noisy in the morning Service they were taken out before the Sermon started, if they were young children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Can you tell me what other social activities, or if not actually social, what other activities were connected with the Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Band of Hope, that was a regular week night activity. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 
Then there were various kinds of classes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Learning what sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Mostly kind of Bible study and things of that nature, but naturally you'd need to be a bit older, preparation for Scripture ex
aminations, and so on. When I was round about 9, 10, 11 we had a club which would be along the lines of the present modern youth club, but it was called Handy Boys' Club, but it was gymnastics and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Carpentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, it was mostly athletic and completely social, you know; rope climbing, vaulting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
So when you got into your teenage years did you spend quite a few evenings in activities connected with the Chapel? Was it an important part of your social life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, no, perhaps 2 to 3 a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And the Shaftesbury Society that presented those books to your parents, that was in no way connected with the Chapel, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 This is a long story. The particular place that my parents worshipped at in.. when we lived in Richmond R
oad - at that period - was connected with a mission hall in a locality known as Haggerston, part of Shoreditch, and my mother and my father threw themselves in with the work down there particularly, and led quite a lot of the activities. And this mission,
 
although it was a Methodist mission and is quite a big mission today, was also affiliated to the Shaftesbury Society. And that's where that part of the work came in. And it was through working for the Shaftesbury Society social work, cripple - visiting an
d such like, that they got their presentation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you have anything to do with that activity at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not directly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you meet any of the poor children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, I met a lot, I met and mixed, but I had no responsibilities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But you met people, perhaps, from backgrounds which you otherwise might not have mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember what sort of impression this made on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 The particular mission in Hillcock Street, Haggerston, was in a very poor quarter, v
ery much a slum quarter and I remember that at the end of the road, end of this narrow street, as it was, there was a public house named The Black Bull, and it seemed to me as a youngster that practically every man that lived down that particular area was
 usually drunk, and I think it gave me a horror of the effects of alcohol. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And that is something that has remained with me all my life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember the children at all, talking to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. Ragged. No shoes, no socks; very largely unwanted 
and neglected. And they used to heard into this mission ... I was going to say in their hundreds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were they fed at all there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Occasionally. There was no regular kitchen there to feed them. The place wasn't large enough for that. It would have be
en condemned, today, from safety regulations and fire precautions. It wouldn't have been allowed today to crowd in the people that were crowded in there. But there it was, it catered for them, and I think lots of the parents round about were glad to have 
the mission there to send their children, particularly on Sunday afternoons as it gave them a break.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Now those sort of children, were they at all round Richmond Road? Did you come across those sort of people ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, no, Richmond Road from Hillcock Street was a good quarter of an hour's walk and it was a different social class altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Could you say that if your parents had not had that connection you would have had very little to do with those children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I wouldn't have seen them, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Although it was only a quarter of an hour's walk away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. There was a canal used to divide Dalston from Haggerston and it was like walking from the West End to the East End, almost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 A different world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did any of those children go to the school that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not even then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Do you remember any other things about the children from a personal point of view? Do you remember ever being made aware that you were a privileged person compared with them, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, I don't think so. There is a certain natural acceptance amongst children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was Grace said at meals when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 All meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Who was it said by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Right round the table, usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You all said it, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember being taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Could you describe them to me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Just a reading, short readi
ng, maybe read by either parent or, as I got older and could read, myself and followed by just a short prayer. Nothing elaborate, nothing very formal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Just a small ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Just a small thing; a daily Bible reading and a daily prayer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was it in the morning or the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
It wasn't regular insofar that it was a fixed kind of thing every day, but at some time during the day, as the time factor allowed it. If Father was really early in the morning we might have prayers after breakfast, but o
therwise perhaps it would be just before I went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Now, your grandfather, your mother's father, had been Chairman of the Conservative }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2184773 &}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  Unionist Party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did your mother take on those views as she grew up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, she was Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was your father the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would you say they were interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Mother very much. Both of them, really, yes. Yes, they both were. I can remember hearing extreme arguments between Mother and friends and even with her own family on politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Because the rest of her family stayed with the Conservatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember anything particularly that your mother argued about, that she felt strongly about?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, free trade, I think, was the great issue of the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about women's suffrage, did she have views on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Oh, yes. I don't think she went to the extent of wholly supporting all the things that the suffragettes did, but she naturally thought women ought to have a better place and a bigger say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did your father hold that view, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Knowing Dad I suppose he had to (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you know if his parents had been Liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I should imagine they were Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So, to the question why he (your father) and she (your mother) held their views, would it be because of their non-conformist ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
That may have had an influence, but quite honestly I couldn't tell you what influenced them to change what had been the family political background.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It's interesting because I believe research shows that most people follow their parents. It's interesting to know why people change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, of course, I don't suppose I was old enough at the time to understand. I should imagine, probably, the mere fact that it was a 
non-conformist ... as you've already noted, it seems that non-conformists, or a lot of non-conformists took the ... what would have been I suppose the Left Wing of that day and became radical.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you actually remember them voting in a general election before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I seem to have vague recollections of them going round and putting bills in doors for their particular candidate. So, yes, they would have voted. I can remember quite a lot of excitement when I was a boy over polling days and the wearin
g of rosettes and that sort of thing, so yes, the answer to your question must be yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were they members of the Liberal Party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you know if they took part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
At that time, as you know, many men felt under pressure to vote the way their employers or the business or the landlord wished them to vote; do you know if your father was ever under that sort of pressure at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Your mother was a Guider?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Was she active in anything else? Obviously a lot of her time would have been in the mission, I suppose. Any other outside activities or interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That would have taken up most of her spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself? Did they ever go out for a ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, yes. Now, let's get this straight. What are we talking about? Are we talking about her, personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Her leisure activities, really, and sort of non-working activities of your parents ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 We haven't touched my other grandparents, have we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. Could you tell me a little about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. My father's parents were originally Somerset folk, came from Yeovil where I think my great-grandparents had a 
glove factory. My grandfather himself was for many years in the Merchant Navy and I believe he sailed on one of the last sailing ships, the iron clad sailing ships. And I can remember visiting them, and I was very fond of visiting them. Unlike my other gr
andfather I was very fond of this one. One of the things I can always remember, he carried out his old sailor's habit, last thing at night he always had his tot of rum and it used to smell the room out. I can smell that rum now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Where were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
They lived in Finsbury Park. And they weren't wealthy, they weren't poor. They were very, very thrifty, and there was nothing elaborate in their home at all, it was reasonable, but nothing elaborate. They were both of them very fond of me and spoilt me. U
n
fortunately, their domestic life wasn't very happy and there was a period in their lives when they both lived in the same house but didn't speak to one another, and if I visited my grandfather I went upstairs to see him in his rooms and I came downstairs 
t
o visit my grandmother. And this went on for some years, but towards the end of their lives there was a reconciliation and they lived together the latter part of their lives quite happily. They were both over 70 when they died, in fact, nearly 80, one of 
t
hem. And they didn't leave any money behind, or very much, or anything like that, just a few pounds. But I will say this, that when my mother was struggling when I was round about the age of 15 to try and give me a little bit more education, finishing off
,
 my grandmother did her best to foot the bill and it was her that also paid for my first piano lessons, that sort of thing. My uncle, her only son, was killed during the War at Cambrai, he was shot by a sniper. He had just won his cap and gown at Cambridg
e
, straight through from a Board school, which was quite a thing in those days when there were no grants and that sort of thing, Grandmother had footed the bill for the whole of his education. It's true he won scholarships, but they had to be backed up by 
the money to keep him in these places and pay for his books and activities, and so on. And then, without really any experience of the world behind him he went out to the War and was killed. He could speak about 6 languages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You said 'their only son', do you mean their only other son?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Only other son, yes, I'm sorry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And no daughters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
No, daughters, no. Yes, sorry. Yes, I had an aunt. Of course I did, I mustn't forget her. Yes, there were the 2 boys, my father was the elder and will was the second one, the uncle that was killed, and then there was this one sister.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember the uncle at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, very well. Yes, I remember him because he was quite boyish, he wanted to be a schoolmaster and said he'd like to have me in his 
school and he'd put me through it, you know, that sort of thing. Yes, he was a very clever young man and I could never hope to follow in his footsteps and I think my grandmother thought I might be able to, that's why she wanted to get me on the road of hi
gher education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That didn't happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Mother couldn't keep it up
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Very hard times for you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Actually, they fade out the picture, really, after that, apart from the fact that it was quite a happy relationship. My mother didn
't get on with either of them very well and so, of course, that kept us very much apart. And the visits that I made, usually my aunt - the one, the daughter, you see - she used to come and collect me. I was very fond of her. And I made most of my visits o
n my own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 From about what age was that that you'd go there on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, quite young. Do you have any idea why they didn't get on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think there was a certain religious bias and also political views, as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were they Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They were nothing. My aunt was Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When you say they were nothing, do you mean they were like so many Londoners, church and chapel meant nothing to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 If they had to define what they were they would probably have put down C. of E., but it meant nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They weren't militant atheists?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, no. No. Literally nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Like so many thousands of Londoners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs? Well, he obviously, I would be right in saying, didn't go to pubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 He wasn't a member of a club, either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The chapel, was it his club, really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 His life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And the same is true of your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did he take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did he ever watch sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you know if he ever betted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would he have considered that wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, definitely. Even a raffle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And I presume that you didn't have playing cards in your house? Would they have considered playing cards wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
No. This is amusing. It was during the early days of the First World War when Mother was working. She worked at a grocer's shop, as an assistant, and she managed the shop when the owner went away down in Devonshire after some of the ra
ids started. And it was during those periods when I was staying in the house, I think there were 3 residents there and I made up the fourth, so to make a fourth player they taught me to play Whist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And what did she think of that, didn't she mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, she played, herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Sorry, I see what you mean. I was thinking of her out at work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, there were 2 others in the house, my mother and me, and they taught me to play Whist to make up the fourth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And you don't remember, then, them feeling that card-playing was ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Oh, no, my father, right up until he died, would always welcome a game of cards. He used to love Cribbage. And yet, of course, they never gambled on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, they may have gambled for match sticks or something like that, but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember other chapel people, whether they had this view on cards, at all, that it was all right if you didn't play for money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 My wife's parents would not tolerate card
s under any circumstances in their house, or anything. But ... consequently to this day I don't think my wife fully understands the hands of cards, or even the suits. But generally speaking I think you'll find that quite a lot of chapel people play cards.
 
They go to Whist Drives and they learn Bridge. Well, my wife's people were strict and particular Baptists, which are Calvinistic in their outlook and poles apart from Methodist. They are very narrow, very rigid. Mind you, she's been a Methodist now for ..
. what? Forty-odd years (laughter).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What was your parents' attitude to the theatre? They didn't consider the theatre immoral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They loved drama.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you go to plays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. I've been to see some farces, when I was a youngster. I can alwa
ys remember one farce. We went to a West End theatre, I can't remember which one it was, but probably the Savoy or one of those, The Private Secretary, it was called. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 
George Robie, I think, was in it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I can remember that one. And being near Hackney we went
 several times to Hackney Empire when there was anything on worth seeing. Not music hall, they weren't keen on music hall and, of course, to the Theatre Royal at Stratford quite a number of times. So they weren't against theatre, provided that it was a re
asonably moral play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Now, the cinema was expanding at that time, did you go to the cinema at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Frequently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Charlie Chaplin, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Pearl White, and, of course, all the Buster Keaton and all that crowd. I can remember ..
. it was a real Saturday afternoon out, because there were other children in this house at Richmond Road. The lady downstairs had got a large family and I used to go with their boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were they friends of yours generally, you know, at other times, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Very friendly. They were very friendly, yes. They didn't share, as I said earlier, they did not share our same outlook but they weren't antagonistic either side. I mean, the mere fact that we had different opinions didn't form a barrier between them
. Generally, from generally living arrangements, everything went very smoothly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And your mother didn't object to your being friendly with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember any children or people who, for various reasons she disliked you to associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You don't remember this happening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not, particularly, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Where did you play when you were in Richmond Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Garden. It was a good sized garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Could you play in the street? You mentioned playing outdoors in Chingford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Well, that was different, it was country. I wasn't allowed to rake the streets. I had to be home from school within a certain time of school closing. Supposing we came out at 4, we were only about 6 or 7 minutes from school
, so I was expected home by quarter past 4 at the latest, or else there were questions asked.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And you weren't allowed to just go wandering off in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So would you say that street playing wasn't part of your childhood, really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember seeing other children playing in the street and wishing you could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, particularly round where the mission was situated, that was the only place they had to play. They had no gardens or yards, only the o
dd play where you put the dustbin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you play with your brother? I suppose you played with him but it was the kind of play of a much younger child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You mentioned having a bicycle at quite an early age and that interested me be
cause so many people hadn't got bicycles when they were much older, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The bicycle was given to me by my grandmother on my father's side after my uncle was killed, in the War. It was his bicycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So you would have been quite young compared with other children at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I suppose so, yes. Let's see, what would I have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 About 10 or 11, I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were you allowed to go cycling off ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Wherever I liked, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 After school could you go off on your bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
This club that I mentioned had a cricket team and, of course, I used to play football. Nothing very serious, we weren't in a league or anything like that, just little friendly matches ... 
little inter-club matches without being in a league. I don't think we ever had the money to kind of properly equip me. I mean I never owned my own cricket bat or cricket bag or anything like that, it was usually club property that you borrowed for the occ
asion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And who did you play against, would it be other chapel players?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Inter-club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I remember your saying that money was very tight when you were very small, and when things got a bit better was there regular }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 pocket money}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  ever?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When t
hey considered that I was old enough I was given a shilling a week, which wasn't a bad sum of money, but out of that I was supposed to provide sufficient to keep myself in certain articles of clothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What? Sort of small articles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Small articles of clothing; ties and socks and handkerchiefs and the like. I'm not sure that it worked out always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Part of their training for independence, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What else did you spend the money on, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Swe
ets, and save up for a little ... what you could to buy presents for parents' birthdays or Christmas. And of course, you could do a lot with a penny in those days. You could get sweets at 4 ozs., even 8 ozs. A penny, certain things like liquorice cuttings
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Because you could buy a farthing's worth of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 A farthing's worth, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about things like your Saturday afternoon cinema ticket, would that come out of your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 pocket money}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 ? Or would they pay for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It would depend, I think
, how wealthy I was. If I could afford it I paid for my own, if I couldn't I cadged it or I worked for it, go errands for somebody, perhaps, on Saturday morning and get a halfpenny or a penny for having done it. There was one period, too, during the War w
h
en mother had charge of this shop when I used to act as a delivery boy. I would be a bit older then. I used to take groceries round and, of course, I used to ... some people were very generous and when they paid for their groceries they'd give me a penny 
or twopence, for having taken them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you get a regular payment for the work, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, just a little yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That was just Saturday mornings, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Saturday mornings, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. We've answered that question once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I know, as far as paid help was concerned, but this is really more to try and map out the sort of neighbours and friends and family. Now, your grandmother in Walthamstow helped out a bit with your younger brother, didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Ah, yes, in her own home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I meant sort of generally helping, you know, in a neighbourly kind of way. What about neighbours or the landlady, did she ever give a hand with anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I suppose if one or the other were ill, being both in the same house they would see what they could do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 For each other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They had friends through the chapel, didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would you say they had any other friends that they made from any other pursuit or at any other time in their lives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
As far as I remember most of Mother's acquaintances, and Father's acquaintances, were people that they'd met in their church ... chapel life, and may have been distant cousins and that sort of thing
 of theirs that they kept up with, but I can't really remember any old friends. I'm trying to think because, I mean all these people I had to address as 'uncle' or 'aunt' and, apart from the people whom I knew at the church who were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 Mrs.\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 , apart from relations I can't really remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about neighbours? Did neighbours, the people who lived on either side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They wouldn't concern us in Hackney. We had neighbours either side of us at Chingford and we were friendly with them. I can't rea
lly remember a lot as to whether we went into each other's houses. I can remember going into the house next door for some period and they gave me my meals. Whether that was when my brother was born or not I don't know. It could well have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember any of them coming into your house, having a cup of tea with your mother and having a chat, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think they might well have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But you don't actually recollect it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Don't actually recollect it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was there any organised entertainment, having some friends from Chapel to tea, you went to their homes occasionally for tea before church?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, and then they'd come back to us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And relations, did they come and you'd visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was this usually for tea or would it be for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think it tended mainly to be for tea. Probably they'd stay on in the evening to a little bit of supper, and go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Thinking back to those early years, how were you aware of social classes? What 
social classes were you aware of as a child, up to the end of the first World War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I suppose, influenced very much by my mother's domestic service background, you were taught that there were people who came of families of very high breeding and, of c
ourse, people who were well off and could afford nice things and had had better education were social superiors. I think the kind of .1. the Victorian class distinction was very marked when I was a child and up to a point people were still talking about '
k
nowing their place'. And although this was gradually getting broken down and getting less and less, there was still quite a lot of it. And my mother, particularly, had an inferiority complex when she thought she was in the presence of anybody socially hig
her than herself, and I think she kept it to the very end of her days. It was her undoing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What do you mean when you say 'it was her undoing'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, she never conquered this fear of meeting people who she considered were superior to her and she 
just went nervous and folded up in their presence. This is very strange because, I mean, she could take a roomful of East End women and she could preside over their meeting and she could keep them in order and talk to them and hold her own, but the moment
 she was confronted, shall we say, by somebody with a little bit of a title or even not as high as that, she just went to bits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you think this worried her? Do you think it made her often nervous about meeting these people? Was she sort of self-conscious about it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I think she was, yes. Here again, I put it down to her parlourmaid days and that sort of things, where she was 'yes, ma'am; no, ma'am'. Curtsey when you go in the room and when you come out the room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It left its mark on her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about your father, what was his attitude to the so-called upper class, or whatever you'd call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 He would be more prepared to ... with due deference, meet them on their own level. Now that sounds a contradiction in terms, but you m
ight know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think I know what you mean, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 He would try to be man-to-man with them, but very, very polite with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you think your mother believed herself to be their equals, these people, but in some way she really was con
scious, she really believed herself not to be as good a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, I don't think she did. She would say that: 'I'm not as good as they are'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But when she said 'good' did she mean what the world counts as good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Materially.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But her sor
t of Christian convictions, this didn't overweigh it ever? Now, you were saying that your mother brought you up to be very conscious of the fact that there was this superior class of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What other sort of classes were you brought up to
 kind of think of? There were those people - people who might have titles, or better educated, then what came next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 We were, of course, always involved ...When I say 'we', as a family, we were always involved with the poorer class. The real down-and-
out type, I suppose and I was thrown together with quite a lot of these young people of both sexes, but mostly female, who frequented out house. It was quite an open house for them. And of course, this ... particularly when I got older, this was when my m
other and father started this mission up in Shoreditch which I spoke to you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3103133\charrsid7630904 about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
off record just now. So one was aware that there were people poorer than ourselves, really destitute people, whereas we had an income which was mainly inadequate but at any ra
te, it fed and clothed us. Then there were the people in the social class above us and then, of course, there were the very rich. Then, I suppose, education was always a marked thing, people who spoke very nicely and used correct English. And one tried to
 copy them, sometimes with very poor results, really, you got the grammar all wrong, but still ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Your mother tried to get you to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about people like the trades people? People who kept the shops round about Hackney?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I think they were treated, more or less, just on ... general acquaintances, you know, they came to the door, they were more or less one of you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You didn't feel them to be below or above you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. Naturally, you have to give them orders because th
at was ... well, that's part of the setup, and if you didn't like their service you would say so, but I don't think there was any attempt to treat them as social inferiors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I wonder if you can remember any particular person, either from the poorer cla
ss, as you called it, or from the so-called upper class whom you met as a child, whom you actually remember as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 This is difficult, I saw such a kaleidoscope of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I just wondered if there were any particular people who came to the 
house fairly frequently, say, the poor people, and how you got along with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I suppose there's about half a dozen people stand out in my memory; people who seemed to have more or less a dominating influence over our lives because they were my moth
er and father's closest friends. Some were artisan class, whereas another couple would be office ... professional ... almost professional class. So I got a fairly good mixture of both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember your parents having any friends who were teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. Or had you any contact with teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I don't think so. I know the person who lived }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 next door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  to my grandmother at Walthamstow, she was a schoolteacher, but she had no influence whatsoever over me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You don't remember mixing with them at all? Teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were you conscious, as a child, of the Church of England and the sort of people who went there, as people are in a small community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Up to a degree, yes. Chapel was Chapel, and Church was Church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think I've got an idea what you mean but could you enlarge a bit on that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
There wasn't a great deal of sympathy between the two. You see, as a child I wouldn't know much about it. I know at Church they had a Creed and a Catechism and things l
ike that that we didn't have within the mission side of the work of the Methodist Church. Since I've grown older I've found that the Methodist setup is very, very closely related to the Church of England and there is the recitation of the Creed and there 
are the Litanies, and so on, and Liturgies because, after all, John Wesley was Church of England. And this is one of the biggest arguments for Methodist union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 As a child the two were poles apart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would you say in any way they were socially apart? Would different sorts of people ... ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, you would find this definitely in village life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about in Hackney, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think in town it settled itself in much the same way that the doctors and the upper social 
class went to the church. There was a church, though, right ... adjacent to the mission premises, All Saints, at Haggerston. And ... of course, it was a very low evangelical church and I suppose, really, had I had the ability to analyse it when I was a ch
ild we would have found that its workings - apart from the fact that it had to keep to the prescribed order laid down by the church, of Evensong and Mattins and the rest of it - its work was very, very similar to the work we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But you didn't have contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember if there were any other groups? Were there any Irish Catholics around that you would have been conscious of in Hackney?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The word 'Catholic' was almost anathema.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 In your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. But there again, as you get older one learns to be more tolerant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you actually remember Catholic people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. I didn't know much about them as a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It was more a word to you than anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It was more a word, yes, they were something poles apart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You weren't conscious of their mission work or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about the Salvation Army, did you have anything to do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, they came into it quite a lot. The Salvation Army were very, very close with the type of work that we were doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
You were describing to me your mother's attitudes to what she considered to be her superiors, and your father's; would you say that people that were poorer than they were, did they have the same att
itude towards those people? You said your father felt a bit more confident with the upper classes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did they feel similar in their attitude to poorer people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, I think they did. Mother wasn't afraid of the poorer people like she ... there was no ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was your father the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, they were very, very genial, I think, to these other people and I think they tried to make them feel comfortable, as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you think they succeeded?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 To a very great extent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 At that time do you remember anybody moving up or down the social scale, as it were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You mean in our family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, could be in your family. I was simply meaning cases of people you knew who sort of went up or went down in the world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Can't remember it. Can't remember anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But you were, I think you said, quite conscious that this was a hope your mother had ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That we would go up, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember your mother actually sort of talking about you in any kind of clas
s label? Your family, whether she would describe you as belonging to a certain class, or wasn't it put into words like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think if she had been asked she would have said that we were in the lower middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 She would have used that expression?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. Whether I heard it at that age, or not ... but I heard it since. Lower middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember anyone being described as 'a real gentleman' or 'a real lady? The actual term used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, but this is a very dangerous phrase.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I wondered what - if you'd heard it mentioned then - you'd thought it might have meant, because it can mean a lot of different things to a lot of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It can mean a lot of different things and I think if they were treated ... Let's put it thi
s way: if somebody superior - or whom she thought was superior - treated them in a very friendly way, or if another person was very generous, or extra courteous, then all these attitudes could be described as being 'a real gentleman' or 'a real lady'. In 
other words, the term, I think, was meant to convey breeding.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 More than money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 More than money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember calling certain people 'sir'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. The schoolmaster, always and anybody whom I hadn't been kind of introduced to or didn't
 know intimately, or these ... all male acquaintances no matter, really, what their social class that I hadn't been instructed to call 'uncle'. If I had no address for them or didn't know their name to call them 'Mr.' or anything like that, I'd call them 
'sir'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And this really would apply to the very poor people, too, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Mostly with those you would know their Christian names, and they were the Christian names we used quite a lot. Bob, or Dick, or someone.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And was this true of your parents and the middle class people, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were you brought up to touch your cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Always, to a lady. Raise your cap, and as I never wore a cap, only for a very short period of my life .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Frequently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They were around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, they used to patrol fairly regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you know them? Know them by name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Not by name. One or two became familiar, particularly round the site of where the miss
ion work was, you got to know the policeman on the beat there. My parents may have known them by name. And they used to patrol in that particular area always in twos.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you mean round Richmond Road, or round the mission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, the mission.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Because of fear of attack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about round Richmond Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, solitary ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember how you thought they treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I'll cut across your question by saying that I was always taught to regard a policeman as a f
riend and that as long as you didn't cross a policeman you'd got nothing to fear from him. And one recognised a policeman, if he really took anybody in charge we was doing it because the person had been doing something wrong and he was preserving the peac
e.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Presumably you weren't aware of how poorer people or drunken people were treated by the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You told me quite a bit about the landlady at Richmond Road. What about at Chingford, that was rented accommodation, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It was a rented house, and we had the whole house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And the landlord ... ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would be an agent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So you didn't have personal contact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet? You talked quite a bit about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Was there quite a change, though, when your father got that job round about 1912, I think you said, after that period of unemployment? Did it make quite a difference to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, I think we were a little better off but it didn't put us in ... We weren't really what you'd call 'comfortably off', ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did they have to get into debt at that time, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think they did. I seem to remember scraps of conversation at the back of my
 mind between my mother and father which I didn't properly understand, but later on I recognised as being discussions on their financial position, which really was referring to money borrowed and paid back, etc.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were they in any clubs, like clothing clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, they used to have clothing clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Sick club, do you know? Doctor's club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Christmas clubs, these slate clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 How were these organised because I used to think they were organised through pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, churches run them as well, you know. Yes. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you ever get any help from the Guardians, or charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I wouldn't know, but I should very much doubt it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you think your parents would have had strong feelings against having to take ... ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 My mother
 was very proud. She'd come in the class today, I think, that although she'd qualify for a rates rebate you'd have a dickens of a job to get her to apply for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember anybody being made to leave the district by having rough music made, by b
anging tin cans outside their door, or making a noise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were you taught anything before you went to school in the way of reading or writing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think there was an attempt to do so, yes. Yes, I think there was. Same as we do today. Both m
y grandchildren, David's children could read more or less before they went to school. Simple things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would that have been your mother or your father, or both, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 How old were you when you first actually went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 About 4, I believe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you actually remember the hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember the hours of any school that you attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They were generally 9 'till 12 and 2 'till 4.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Now, your first school, would that have been ... ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 We we
re living in Richmond Road and my first school would have been Wilton Road, Hackney, the infants' school. And of course, I was transferred when we moved to South Chingford to the infants' school in New Road, South Chingford. Then I went back again to the 
boys' school at Wilton Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That would have been elementary schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, elementary schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And then you spoke about when you were 15, your grandmother helping you with money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, I went to Parminter's in Victoria Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Is that a foundation ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
We have a clash of dates here. Fourteen, 131/2 to 14 I went to Parminter's, I should say, because I started out to work just before I was 15.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So you were there for only a short while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Only a very short while and then Father's accident ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Put paid to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Which school of the schools you went to do you remember the most clearly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Wilton Road. I remember fairly clearly the latter part of my time at New Road, South Chingford. It was quite a countr
y school. I remember I was quite happy there. But most of my schooling was at Wilton Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 How near was that to your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Seven to 10 minutes, shall we say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And you walked, presumably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Both ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When you started school did you go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 In the infants I would have been taken by my mother, and met.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you come home to dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. There were no school meals in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I know that, I just wondered if you took something with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Mostly you went to the school that was fairly near to your house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
By and large I liked it. Naturally, one had likings for certain of the teachers in preference to others, but by and large I liked school. It was always an ambition, of course, to get into the school }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 next door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
, which was the central school or, better than that, to get into a grammar school. But because of my age and the way I fitted in with the rules governing entrances for scholarships - I missed my scholarship at 
11, and again the following year I missed it. I think through illness, or something. And so I never took a scholarship. I sat for a trades scholarship when I was 13 but I didn't get it. That would have sent me to a technical college. Otherwise I have no a
cademic successes whatsoever to claim, I just muddled along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would you have stayed at school longer, from your own personal point of view?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I would have stayed longer ... I said 'my father's accident', but this must have been my father's illness, 
the breakdown I spoke about, why I left Parminter's. Because they couldn't afford to keep the fees going. I'm not sure what the financial circumstances were at the time, whether he was stopped for this long illness or what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Was Parminter's a grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Parminter's was a grammar school. It's a foundation school, yes. People with low incomes could get in at a lower fee than people with higher incomes and, of course, we got in at a reasonable fee, but Mother still couldn't afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Is that the grammar school to which you would have gone had you passed the scholarship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I don't think so. I think I would have gone to the Grocers School at Hackney Downs. That was more the usual one that followed on from the schools in Hackney, they went to the Grocers School. Or Christchurch, that was the other one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember what the teachers emphasised as important in school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Reading, writing, arithmetic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And apart from that, on the general behaviour side of things, do you remember what they ... ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 On what particular things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Silence in class; learning by rote and having a good memory to repeat what you'd learnt, and they were very, very quick to use a ruler or their own hands if they felt that
 you hadn't given attention to either a lesson or their instructions. They were terribly sarcastic, a lot of them. Others were quite nice, and of course, you didn't mix your teachers. You'd one teacher who took you right through the lessons. You had that 
t
eacher as long as you were in his class, for everything, excepting perhaps music ... singing, when you went out into the hall and one of the ... it might have been a school mistress there who took singing. Apart from that everything else was by the one te
acher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
You were telling me about your mother's efforts to get you to speak differently, was there any of that in the school? Any campaign by the teachers to get the children not to speak in a sort of London accent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You'd be pulled up if you said 'shan't' or 'won't' or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You mean you had to say 'shall not'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 '}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 Shall not}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 '.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They wanted you to be exact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, but to try, I think, and stop slang as much as anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Language more than accent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about punctuality, was that very strictly ... ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Yes, if you were late, if I remember rightly, you were sent to stand in the hall. You were not allowed in your class for, say, 15 minutes after the time classes had started, by which time the headmas
ter had made his inspection of all the people in the hall. If a person was continuously late, then he usually got the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did they ask what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes, they were very concerned if you brought home a bad report.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did they ever visit the school? Either that one or the Chingford one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 They may have gone up to ... just seen the teacher if anything specific had arisen, but we didn't have anything like Ope
n Days or parents' associations or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You don't have any recollection of them meeting the teachers, then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Only if they went up for some specific reason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Generally speaking, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Both in social class and in behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I don't think I could judge that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You were saying that there was this canal and the two sides were rather different; you didn't have ... ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 We didn't have the children from the other side of the canal, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about better-off children, from people with a higher income?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 There would be some of those at the school but we mixed up and I don't think, as children, that we took much notice one of another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about the teachers, did they favour one or ... ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I think the teachers had their favourites, the same as they always do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were the favourites because of intelligence or because of class, or both, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The way you behaved, I think, as much as anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about gangs or cliques, do you remember them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes. Yes, there were little groups of us that always kind of ... could be found together, and there were always the little rival ones.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember them being based on anything like streets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I suppose they were. Streets, mainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You do actually remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 At school, I think, yes, there were ... or classes. You'd find ... shall we say Standard 3 would have nothing to do with Standard 4, and
 so on. We were standards in those days, not classes. It was something to go up into the next standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you remember any children who were left out of things, on their own? Persistently, I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 This is very hard to say. I'm not sure. I haven
't a vivid recollection. I suppose in every community ... at least, it's been my experience to find that in every community you've got your one backward child who becomes the butt of the rest, and is always the one that's not particularly welcome.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But you don't actually remember it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Do you know if there were workhouse children who attended the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You were, I think you said, 15 when you actually finished your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 About that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you go to any evening classes or anything of that kind later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I did, later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Can you tell me about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I didn't go for a year or two. Partly at my Father's instigation. I think they would have liked me to have gone into the Methodist ministry and I hadn
't got the necessary background education. And so I went trying to study in order to get matriculation, which I never got, incidentally. I found it very, very difficult to go back - I'd left school some years, several years - and I found it very, very dif
f
icult at the age of 18 or 19 to go back to do just ordinary school subjects, algebra and the like. I'd never been particularly clever at them. But prior to that I'd been to a technical evening class where I'd taken a ... about 18 months, I suppose I was t
h
ere, a course in instrument-making where I learnt to use a lathe and use tools, metal tools, cut out odd legs and calipers and things like that. And then, when this idea of going into the ministry came along, as I say, I went to evening classes and I trie
d
 to learn those and I also took the course in New Testament Greek. And then the whole ... kind of tenor and outlook of my life changed and my work ... The job that I had folded up at the time and then I got into the accountancy profession by very devious 
sort of means and then, of course, I started seriously studying accountancy. And I stayed in the accountancy profession until I retired a couple of years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What sort of position did you reach? When you say you started seriously studying do you mean you took exams?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I stayed in professional accounting, a professional office, for 14 years. And then I had an opportunity and I branched out, took a chance, and I became accountant-secretary to a social service institute. That job folded up after about
 18 months but it led me ... during that time I'd made several social contacts and I got in touch with Sir James Hawkey and also a Mr. Perry who was the Secretary of the Industrial Welfare Association and knew them both very, very well, indeed and through
 
their ... that was when I was in the Social Service Institute, and through them I managed to get an interview with the Chief Accountant of the London Electricity Board and I got into the electricity industry and stayed with them for 30 years and I ended u
p
 as principal assistant to the Chief Accountant. So although I'm not a qualified professional accountant I've had very wide accountancy experience. You see, with my lack of educational background and the fact that when I was in an accountant's office over
 
40 years ago, when I first started, the only thing that was open to me then was to become a chartered accountant or an incorporated accountant. And to be a chartered accountant you had to have money because you had 5 years articles for which you received 
o
n pay whatsoever, besides paying a heavy premium and that was entirely out of the question. You could sit for the incorporated exams and you had to have 7 years in the profession. You must have at least matriculation standard to exempt you from the prelim
inary, or you'd got to take the equivalent of matriculation by taking their preliminary examinations. There again, I felt I was too old to ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Start on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 To get on to that. And of course, here again the whole setup was different between maste
r and man. You were kind of convinced by your employer that it didn't matter unless you'd got a big connection and could set up in practice on your own, it really wasn't worth the trouble of going through and qualifying. I've always regretted it because I
 think I could have gone very, very much higher after nationalization of the electricity industry than I did. But nevertheless, I'm not grumbling, I didn't do too badly, in the end.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What did you do up to when you became an accountant? What was your first job after leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
I had 3 in a week. One applied for a junior clerk and the first one I went to was in a shipping office and, strangely enough, I started there on a Monday and I think the end of the week came on a Wednesday and they paid 
me. And when we calculated this money we decided that they'd paid me short. Mind you, my salary was about 12/6 per week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That was quite a lot for a boy starting because a lot of boys were getting about 7 bob, weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Oh, yes, it wasn't bad
, you know, it was ... And when we worked it out and I went back and challenged it I was told by the chief cashier that they paid on a 7-day week basis. So my father said 'that's not good enough. If you do that they can make you work Saturdays, overtime a
s much as they like, or take you in on a Sunday'. But all day Saturday. So he said, 'no, that won't do' so I didn't go back to them any more. I went out the next day and got a job with Carter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 Paterson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 . I stayed there one day for which I didn't get paid, I
 didn't like it. They put me in a stable over the horses - all their vehicles were horse-drawn - and all I was doing all day long was standing at a splintery bench sorting out }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 the carmen's}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  delivery notes. That wasn't what I wanted to do. And then I got a job with an insurance broker and I stayed with him for about 2 1/2 years. But I had all those 3 jobs in one week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The insurance broker was clerical work, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That was clerical work, most interesting. I became a junior broker while I was there, I
 had a ticket for Lloyds. Quite interesting, but they folded up, they went bankrupt. And from there I got a job with a building society who were not doing very good business but I stayed with them quite a while until they, in turn, went into dissolution, 
w
hich is another way of saying that they wound up. And the accountants that had the job of doing this dissolution chose me out of the remaining staff to go with the books to give them certain information regarding the ... And actually I wound the thing up.
 And that gave me my entrance into the accountancy profession, and as I say, I stayed 14 years in the profession and then 30 years in the chief accountant's department of the London Board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 When you first started, after you left Carter Paterson, what would you have been described as in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Junior clerk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 You were never what they called an office boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I went as an office boy to that first job, the shipping firm. Then it was junior clerk. I can't remember whether the insurance broke
rs advertised for an office boy or a junior clerk. But I became junior clerk, and junior broker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Could you also tell me what your brother's jobs were, not necessarily in so much detail?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 My brother had a rather unfortunate career. As a boy he developed some kind }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3103133\charrsid7630904 
of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 disease}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904  or ... it wasn't a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 disease}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 , exactly, but he had an illness which gave him a lot of headache and it wasn't sure at one time whether he'd even got a tumour. And he was off from school for a long, long while and his education was v
ery, very poor indeed. Eventually, after going a round of hospitals one of the specialists at the Hospital for Nervous Disorders at Queen's Square discovered, I think, that there was a blocked duct to the brain and by means of lumber punch and things like
 
that they managed to clear the surplus fluid from his brain, and without actually doing brain surgery they got this thing working. And after that he got on, but it was a bit too late. And for a long time, when he first started out at work he just did any 
k
ind of job that he could do. He worked in a builder's yard; he worked as a commercial traveller. He joined the Territorials and it was whilst he was a commercial traveller - about his third job as a commercial traveller - War broke out and being a territo
r
ial he became one of the first to be called up. He was in the R.A.M.C. and he stayed with the R.A.M.C. until he was demobbed at the end of the War. But while he was in the Army he made quite good use of his opportunities and he went on quite a number of e
d
ucational courses and, egged on by his wife, I think, he put his name down for one particular medical course and they told him he hadn't got the necessary qualifications to enter for this. But he pursued it right the way through to the commanding officer 
s
aying that the notice posted on the notice board gave no conditions of entry, it was a free notice. The commanding officer said, 'well, let him go through, he won't last 5 minutes. He hasn't got these qualifications, he's bound to fall down on the exam'. 
S
trangely enough, he came somewhere near the top, if not the top when he took the exam and he found himself as a registered medical auxiliary. And from there he took practical examinations and theory examinations and he's now ... for some years, now, since
 the War he's bad his own business as a chiropodist and masseur.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 That's quite a triumph, really, after such an unhappy start.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It is. He's built up quite a good. And he's become ... he isn't now because he found it was too worrying, but he became 
hospital consultant in chiropody. He had dealing with diabetic patients who so easily turn to gangrene, you know, and he had decisions to make as to whether a limb should be amputated and so on. It was getting him down a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But he enjoyed the work generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 The work, he didn't mind the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about your wife, die she have a job before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 My wife was a milliner. She trained as a milliner and he ended up by being designer, millinery designer with her own table}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3103133\charrsid7630904 s..}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 . with apprentices of her own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And after marriage did she work at all for money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 No, only for me (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 And David, has he always been in academic jobs, or has he had other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 David has come right the way through from school, he's not worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 He's always been in the academic life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. I mean, apart from vacation jobs which students do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 But his career has always been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It's uninterrupted career and it's all been educational.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you belong to any professional organisation or trade union at any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Yes. N.A.L.G.O.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were you an active union member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 At one time I was chairman of the branch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Were you active over quite a long period, even when you weren't chairman, I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 A number of ye
ars, but I was only chairman for roughly 18 months because of a reorganisation within the industry when we were de-centralised, and I was sent from the chief accountant's department in headquarters in the City down to Ilford where a chief accountant's dep
artment was set up in my charge at the local accounting centre. And I became the liaison between headquarters and the local accounting centre. And then, of course, having moved right out of the area I had to give up my branch chairmanship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you feel that there was a conflict between employers and workers in the sort of way of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
Yes. I suppose at that particular time NALGO was not a very militant trade union in fact, we weren't affiliated at that particular time to the Trades Union Congress,
 but one ... I think the biggest point of difference between employer and employee at that time was, following nationalization people were supposed to be graded according to their job and this is where the big dispute came in. And it was the unfairness on
 
appeals committees and the terrific waste of time dragging through various structures of committees to get appeals heard, and the ... actually, often, the inadequate briefing of NALGO itself as to the setup within the industry to allow them to get a compr
ehensive picture of what the whole dispute was about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Did you ever feel there was a difference between trained craftsmen and other workers in any job, in any kind of thing you were involved in?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Presumably, as a white-collar 
worker you wouldn't have had very much to do with this. This applies more to people who have worked on the shop floor. Perhaps in any other walks of life, you know ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 There was always a kind of friendly ... more or less friendly rivalry between cler
ical workers and engineers in the industry who did a certain amount of paperwork. We were inclined to kind of depreciate the efforts of the engineer to do clerical work, and there was a little conflict here. Sometimes it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 good-natured}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 , sometimes it was a little bit bitter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 What about their attitude to the full clerical workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Well, they never thought we did any work of any importance. Ours was non-productive, in any case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 So that was the distinction that you felt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 It was reciprocal, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
What we sometimes ask is whether the skilled man and the unskilled man were sort of in conflict or felt this, but of course, you probably didn't come across that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 I didn't come in touch very much with the unskilled man. I came across th
e engineers; storekeepers, occasionally. But wiremen and the like, they had their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16057785\charrsid7630904 foreman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
, and that and I very rarely had any contact with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5470496 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 Would you say that fulltime work changed your general attitude to life in anyway? When you actually started working, after you left school?

\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid5470496 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6171968 FL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5533864\charrsid7630904 
My parents had always stressed the value of less money for a secure job, and apart from a very short period in my life I have always been fully employed and I've been very grateful for it. And looking back I suppose 
there are moment when I would have very much liked to have a more adventuresome and more colourful sort of life, but of course, I'm now reaping the fruits of the ... shall we say the years of monotony by the things that a secure job has ...
\par }}